  "voiceover": "You'll hear it often: Jesus never actually claimed to be God. But he did. Let's take a closer look — in his own words and deeds. He said, 'Before Abraham was born, I AM' — taking up God's own name from Exodus — and his hearers picked up stones, because they knew exactly what he meant. He forgave sins, something only God can do. He accepted worship instead of refusing it. He said, 'I and the Father are one,' and 'Anyone who has seen me has seen the Father.' When Thomas said, 'My Lord and my God,' Jesus didn't correct him. Now, some point out that John's Gospel was written later — a fair objection. But Jesus forgave sins and accepted worship in the earliest Gospels too. These aren't the words of a mere moral teacher. They're the claim of God in the flesh.",
  "source": "answers/did-jesus-claim-to-be-god.html",
